    "description": "We at Lupin Asia Pacific Associates are looking for an experienced Medical Officer based out of Bengaluru. If you are a result-oriented professional with a passion for excellence, we want to hear from you.\n\nAbout Lupin Asia Pacific Associates:\nLupin Asia Pacific Associates is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Provide high-quality patient care and maintain patient records\n• Adhere to NABH/JCI accreditation standards\n• Diagnose and treat medical conditions following established protocols\n• Collaborate with pharmaceutical representatives and medical suppliers\n• Coordinate with multidisciplinary teams for comprehensive patient management\n• Administer medications and treatments as prescribed\n• Monitor patient progress and adjust treatment plans accordingly\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Arch / M.Arch from recognized institution\n• 1-3 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in CPT Codes\n• Proficiency in Health Informatics\n• Proficiency in Wound Care\n• Proficiency in Infection Control\n• Proficiency in Diagnostic Skills\n• Proficiency in Medical Coding\n• Proficiency in EMR/EHR\n• Proficiency in Medical Terminology\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Referral bonus program\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Annual performance appraisal\n• Salary Range: 4 LPA - 9 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Bengaluru, Karnataka, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Lupin Asia Pacific Associates!",
